editorialSummary.text: Burgers & hot dogs whipped up with creative toppings in an unpretentious locale with outdoor tables.

text.text:
"Burger Blenger is truly the best burger in its class, hands down! The lines are always long, especially during holiday seasons like this. The taste is incredibly delicious, with a generously thick patty and they're definitely not stingy with the sauces. Basically, you'll be eating with sauce all over your face! The price is also quite reasonable.

What's a bit puzzling is why they don't seem to want to open more branches. I'm sure they'd be packed! Or maybe they're focused on maintaining quality? It's not about being everywhere, it's about keeping the quality consistent and ensuring loyal customers always come back. Well, it's definitely worth the wait!"

text.text:
As a catfish lover, I was really curious about this catfish fillet. When I arrived, the line was long, but the service was fast because the waiter was frying it all the time.

The idea is interesting. The catfish was delicious yesterday, but for some reason, it tasted very salty to me, both in the crunchiness, the coating, and the meat itself. So I didn't really enjoy the catfish fillet.

The chili sauce was all devil's chili, so spicy, it kept my eyes open.

A portion of catfish fillet and rice was only IDR 20,000, totally worth it. You can pay cash or via QRIS. A must-try if you're in the Pondok Labu area.

I'll try another dish next time, hopefully it won't be too salty.

originalText.text:
Sebagai pecinta lele, penasaran bgt sama lele fillet ini, pas nyampe antrinya panjang, tapi pelayanannya cepet, karena abangnya goreng terus.

Idenya menarik, lelenya juga enak kemarin, cuma entah kenapa, di saya terasa sangat asin, baik kriukannya, coatingnya, juga daging lelenya, jadi akhirnya kurang menikmati lele filletnya.

Sambelnya yg tipe cabe setan semua, pedes banget, merem melek pokonya deh.

1 porsi lele fillet dan nasi cuma Rp. 20.000, worth it banget, bs bayar cash atau QRIS. Harus dicoba si kalo pas di area pondok labu.

Next masih mau coba menu lain, smoga udah ga terlalu asin yaa,

text.text:
Sorry to say, I think this is overrated. I was really curious because all the reviews said it was delicious. Maybe I just got unlucky.

When I tried the catfish, the fillet was super thin and mostly flour-coated. The catfish was also still a bit dry and not very fresh. The coating tasted very salty.

The batter tasted like salted breadcrumbs.

I think the chili sauce is still pretty good, quite spicy. But unfortunately, there were a lot of chili peppers in my chili sauce yesterday, making it a bit tricky to eat.

This is my first time eating dry food, but it tasted really dry.

Hopefully, this will be a point for improvement in the future. üôÇ

it turns out delicious!! text.text:
First time trying Chickin-san because I watched ripiu from Juan Owen and Mamank Kuliner. Parking is very limited, because it is integrated with Cooler City. I happened to come there was a car stopped in front of it so I parked at Indomaret. Chickin-san is on the 2nd floor of Cooler City. So enter the cooler city first and go up to the 2nd floor on the right. 

First come and order the menu, you can Qris and also cash as long as you have the right amount. After paying, you can sit in two places, indoor (AC) and outdoor (smoking area). For the indoor area there are 5 tables and also a high table facing the street. 

When waiting for food it doesn't take long, maybe around 5-7 minutes. I came on a weekday around 4 o'clock and it was quiet. Here the concept is self-service. So when our name is called, we can take our order to our own table. And when you're done eating, tidy up the plates and glasses on the tray, then give them to the employees. 

I ordered Spicy Chickin Rice for 28 thousand. There are choices of sambal, namely matah, korek, and cheese. If you buy ocha here, there is a free refill. Ice box and thermos are provided for the ocha (near the cutlery). For the taste, for me it was too spicy, but it was still enjoyable. The portion is large, quite filling. But unfortunately, because there are a lot of side dishes, the rice was finished first üòÅüòÑ

Overall, this is according to my expectations and does not disappoint. Thank you Chikin-san, hopefully you can increase the number of outlets! Continued success! ü•∞‚ú®Ô∏è

originalText.text:
Pertama kali cobain Chickin-san karena nonton ripiu dari Juan Owen dan Mamank Kuliner. Untuk tempat parkir terbatas banget, karena nyatu sama Cooler City. tadi kebetulan saya datang ada mobil berhenti di depan situ jadinya sy parkir di Indomaret. Tempat Chickin-san ini ada di lt. 2 Cooler City. jadi masuk ke cooler city dulu naik ke lt. 2 di sebelah kanan.

Pertama datang langsung pesan menu, bisa Qris dan bisa juga cash asalkan uangnya pas. setelah bayar bisa duduk di dua tempat, indoor (AC) dan outdoor (smoking area). Untuk ruangan indoor ada 5 meja dan juga meja tinggi yang menghadap jalanan.

Saat menunggu makanan tidak membutuhkan waktu yang lama, mungkin sekitar 5-7 menitan. saya datang weekday sekitar jam 4an dan memang kondisinya sedang sepi. di sini konsepnya self service. jadi ketika nama kita dipanggil, bisa ambil pesanan ke meja sendiri. dan apabila sudah selesai makan, rapihkan piring dan gelas di atas nampan, lalu berikan ke karyawannya.

saya memesan Spicy Chickin Rice seharga 28ribu. ada pilihan sambal yaitu matah, korek, dan cheese. jika membeli ocha di sini free refill. disediakan box ice dan termos untuk ochanya (dekat alat makan). untuk rasa, bagi saya terlalu pedas, tetapi masih bisa dinikmati. porsinya besar, cukup mengenyangkan. namun sayang, karena lauknya banyak jadi nasinya sudah ludes duluanüòÅüòÑ

overall ini sesuai ekspetasi saya dan tidak mengecewakan. thank you Chikin-san, semoga bisa perbanyak outletnya ya! sukses terus! ü•∞‚ú®Ô∏è

text.text: Found this from other side content on TikTok. Because it's close to my dad's house, I'll go straight to the gas. This is the location on the 2nd floor of Ice Cream, not JNE. The minus is that there is no parking space, if you dine in, park in the Alfa/Indo front.

text.text:
I booked a yoga class for three people, myself and two friends, through the website. However, only one of us received a booking confirmation. I reached out to Customer Service via WhatsApp to clarify, and unexpectedly, they informed me that the class had been cancelled, even though it's still being shown as available on the website.

Instead of offering a proper resolution, they said the refund would be issued in the form of app balance or a voucher, and that I would have to rebook the class myself, they couldn‚Äôt assist with rescheduling.

Without further discussion, they issued a refund via a voucher that could only be redeemed once, meaning I couldn't rebook for all three of us. Since then, Customer Service has stopped responding entirely.

This whole experience has been really unprofessional and frustrating. Poor communication, misleading information on the website, and lack of proper customer support are unacceptable.

Update: The management team handled this case very well. The manager named AMBO gave three of us complimentary items, and the Customer service staff apologised to us. I‚Äôm glad the management team has taken this problem seriously. Thank you. I might visit that place more often since they are actually hearing complaints and being responsible for it.  Also, amience is amazing and everything is clean.

text.text:
I‚Äôm a regular at this place and there‚Äôs really nothing in the area quite like it. I work out upstairs and get some munchies downstairs. It has a homey atmosphere and the menu is quite unique.

My favorite thing to get would be:

- Lelepe‚Äôe Haya, easily described as Indonesian tacos, made from what I would guess is tapioca starch hence the chewy texture and topped with (in simple terms) tuna dabu-dabu. It‚Äôs light, bright, punchy, spicy, and filling. It‚Äôs the safest option if you carefully watch what you eat.

Other than that, I also enjoy most of what I have tried:

- Klepon Misu-Misu: Klepon but with coffee cream and biscuit crumbs, can easily be shared with 3 people
- Nasi Goreng Buntel: Bold, sweet, savory, good for when you‚Äôre super hungry because portion size and the richness will fill you up
- Gohu Tuna: Another light option. Complex raw tuna salad with uniquely Indonesian ingredients. Nothing quite like it.
- Tumis Toge Se‚Äôi: Not your usual stir fried beansprout. The smokiness elevates this dish, there‚Äôs just a unique edge to it.

My husband also loves their Mie Goreng Djawa.

If I have to suggest anything for them to improve, it would be the waiting time for the food to come out. But you can feel that each dish that comes out of the kitchen was made with a lot of care, but as a heads up prepare to wait for a little bit for your food to come out.

text.text:
A cozy place, with spacious outdoor and indoor area, to hang out in Pangkalan Jati, Cinere.

Pola Rasa serve Indonesian cuisine. I ordered a savoury Bubur Opor (highly recommended, but only available until 11 am) and Roti Maryam (the canai and kari taste really good).
Kopi jahe and matcha latte = must try!
